article.description: Devon Goodman had 18 points as Penn defeated Cornell 79-73 on Sunday.
article.headline: Penn beats Cornell 79-73 for fifth straight victory
article.linkText: Penn beats Cornell 79-73 for fifth straight victory
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- Devon Goodman had 18 points as Penn defeated Cornell 79-73 on Sunday. Max Martz and Jordan Dingle added 17 points each for the Quakers. Martz also had seven rebounds. AJ Brodeur had 10 points, nine rebounds and eight assists for Penn (12-7, 4-2 Ivy League), which won its fifth consecutive game. The Quakers are tied with Brown for third place behind Ivy co-leaders Yale and Princeton (both 5-1). Josh Warren scored a career-high 23 points and had seven rebounds for the Big Red (5-14, 2-4). Terrance McBride added 15 points. Jimmy Boeheim had 13 points and Bryan Knapp 12. Penn takes on Brown at home on Friday. Cornell plays Harvard on the road on Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
